org.apache.streams.local.queues

Class ThroughputQueue<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.streams.local.queues.ThroughputQueue<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>, BlockingQueue<E>, Queue<E>, ThroughputQueueMXBean

    public class ThroughputQueue<E>
extends Object
implements BlockingQueue<E>, ThroughputQueueMXBean
    A BlockingQueue implementation that allows the measure measurement of how data flows through the queue. Is also a MBean so the flow statistics can be viewed through JMX. Registration of the bean happens whenever a constructor receives a non-null id.

    !!! Warning !!! Only the necessary methods for the local streams runtime are implemented. All other methods throw a NotImplementedException.
